column12: Ranges from 0 - 4. "Don't know" responses coded as incorrect responses. These questions were not asked in 1992. Questions include "Chlamydia only infects females (false)", "Sharing needles does not increase risk for hepatitis C (false)", "Chlamydia can lead to infertility (true)" and "Once caught, a person will always have genital herpes (true)". Variation of wording in different survey years.
column17: Ranges from 0 - 6. "Don't know" responses coded as incorrect. Questions include "Can HIV be spread through coughing and sneezing (no)?", "Can HIV be spread by mosquitoes (no)?", "Does the pill protect against HIV (No)?", "Can condoms help protect against HIV (yes)?", "Can someone with HIV who looks healthy pass on the virus (yes)?", and "Can HIV be transmitted by sharing needles". Wording variation in some surveys.
